$ CSS: font-size property 
@ font-size

The value of the `font-size` property specifies the desired height of → design/font/glyph[glyphs].

Possible values include:
code {
font-size: xx-small
font-size: x-small
font-size: small
font-size: medium
font-size: large
font-size: x-large
font-size: xx-large

font-size: smaller
font-size: larger

font-size: 125%

font-size: 14pt

font-size: 1.3em
code }

  `font-size: 10` tells to use a font whose

sa:

  The `font-size-adjust` property.

  → development/web/CSS/properties
